    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-07-25T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-07-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="504"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d504">
                <head>504. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Egypt</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d504fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 874.2614/7–2556. Official Use Only. Received at 7:30 p.m. Repeated to
                        Moscow and London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-07-25T19:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1956—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>135. From <persName corresp="#p_HPT1">Hart</persName>. Reference <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 119.<note n="2" xml:id="d504fn2">The
                        Embassy in Cairo reported in telegram 119, July 23, that Soviet Ambassador
                        Kisselev had met with <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName> on
                        July 22. <hi rend="italic">Al Ahram</hi> reported that Kisselev had informed
                            <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName> that the Soviet Union
                        would honor its pledge to Egypt to finance the Aswan High Dam project as
                            <persName corresp="#p_SDT1">Shepilov</persName> had made clear in his
                        statement. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> 974.61/ 7–2356)</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName> met for 2 hours with Kisselev
                    last night. Meeting attended by 3 “Soviet officials” and Min State for Planning
                    Boghdadi. No statement. However earlier in day Kisselev told press “I reiterate
                    what Soviet <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SDT1">Shepilov</persName> has already said that Soviet
                    Govt is prepared finance High Dam scheme if Egypt requests such financing”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BHA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Byroade</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
